    • Method Detail

      • retrieveTransactionMetaData

        @Deprecated
TransactionMetaDataResponse retrieveTransactionMetaData(TransactionMetaDataParameters transactionMetaDataParameters)
        Deprecated. since 6.5.0.1.a
        Retrieves meta-data information related to a transaction. The information required to submit along with the transactionMetaDataParameters parameter and the returned TransactionMetaDataResponse properties will vary according to the processing rules. For example during a "discovery" processing rule, the TransactionMetaDataParameters would require to provide the checkoutToken value and the returned TransactionMetaDataResponse would contain the information related to the checkoutToken along with the next processing rule. Some of the calls to retrieveTransactionMetaData(TransactionMetaDataParameters) might require providing the TransactionMetaDataParameters.setExecutingFlowRule(com.paydiant.android.core.enums.transactionflow.TransactionFlowRule). This method provides the provides the polling implementations for eligible flow rules. (i.e.; Flow rules with TransactionFlowRuleSpecification.isExecuteRuleAndPollForResult() value is set to true).
        Parameters:
        transactionMetaDataParameters - transaction meta data parameters containing checkout token value, paydiant reference id, receipt/offer search parameters along with the current execution rule. These parameter properties would be mandatory or optional depending on the next execution rule.
        Returns:
        meta data information related to the provided transaction meta data parameters.
        Throws:
        PaydiantException - PaydiantException or an instance of a child PaydiantException class with the status codes defined here.

      • retrieveTransactionMetaDataWithoutPolling

        TransactionMetaDataResponse retrieveTransactionMetaDataWithoutPolling(TransactionMetaDataParameters transactionMetaDataParameters)
        Retrieves meta-data information related to a transaction. The information required to submit along with the transactionMetaDataParameters parameter and the returned TransactionMetaDataResponse properties will vary according to the processing rules. For example during a "discovery" processing rule, the TransactionMetaDataParameters would require to provide the checkoutToken value and the returned TransactionMetaDataResponse would contain the information related to the checkoutToken along with the next processing rule. Some of the calls to retrieveTransactionMetaData(TransactionMetaDataParameters) might require providing the TransactionMetaDataParameters.setExecutingFlowRule(com.paydiant.android.core.enums.transactionflow.TransactionFlowRule). This method does not perform polling like the retrieveTransactionMetaData(TransactionMetaDataParameters) method, and app developers are required to implement the necessary polling mechanisms for eligible flow rules.
        Parameters:
        transactionMetaDataParameters - transaction meta data parameters containing checkout token value, paydiant reference id, receipt/offer search parameters along with the current execution rule. These parameter properties would be mandatory or optional depending on the next execution rule.
        Returns:
        meta data information related to the provided transaction meta data parameters.
        Throws:
        PaydiantException - PaydiantException or an instance of a child PaydiantException class with the status codes defined here.

        * @since 6.5.0.1.a

      • updateTransaction

        TransactionResponse updateTransaction(TransactionParameters transactionParameters)
        Updates the current transaction with the required offer information, payment tender information, tip amounts, cash back/cash access information, transaction confirmation etc.. The information provided will vary according to the processing rules. (E.g.: "submit offers" processing rule will require any selected offers for a given transaction and "submit offers and payment tenders" rule would need to provide both selected offers and the payment instrument.
        Parameters:
        transactionParameters - the transaction parameters containing offers, payment tender information, tip amounts, cash back/cash access information, transaction confirmation etc.. required for the next processing rule.
        Returns:
        the transaction response containing necessary transaction information along with the current/next processing rules.
        Throws:
        PaydiantException - PaydiantException or an instance of a child PaydiantException class with the status codes defined here.
